Privacy Policy
Pour la version Française de notre Politique de confidentialité, veuillez visiter
https://corp.flipp.com/legal-politique-de-confidentialite/
. In case of discrepancy between the original English version of this Privacy Policy and the French version, the English version prevails.
PLEASE READ THIS FLIPP OPERATIONS INC. PRIVACY POLICY (“PRIVACY POLICY”) WHICH IS PART OF THE FLIPP OPERATIONS INC. LICENSED APPLICATIONS TERMS AND CONDITIONS OF USE AND LICENSED APPLICATION END USER LICENSE AGREEMENT (COLLECTIVELY “TERMS OF USE”) CAREFULLY.  THIS PRIVACY POLICY PERTAINS TO YOUR (“YOU”) ACCESSING AND USING THE FLIPP.COM WEBSITE, THE REEBEE.COM WEBSITE, ANY DOMAIN OWNED & OPERATED BY FLIPP THAT LINKS TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY, THE FLIPP IPHONE/IPAD APP, THE REEBEE IPHONE/IPAD APP, THE FLIPP ANDROID APP, THE REEBEE ANDROID APP, FLIPP SERVICES OFFERED THROUGH THIRD PARTIES, INTERACTIONS BETWEEN USERS, FLIPP, CONSUMER PACKAGED GOODS COMPANIES (“CPGs”), FOODSERVICES COMPANIES, AND RETAILERS IN STORES AND AT THE POINT OF PURCHASE, AND FLIPP SOCIAL MEDIA ACCOUNTS INCLUDING ALL CONTENT AVAILABLE THROUGH THESE VARIOUS PLATFORMS (COLLECTIVELY “SERVICE”). ANY REFERENCE TO ‘FLIPP’ OR ‘WE’ OR ‘US’ HEREIN SHALL REFER TO FLIPP OPERATIONS INC. AND/OR ANY OR ALL OF ITS AFFILIATES.
The Service is operated by Flipp Operations Inc. (“We” or “Us”). This Privacy Policy describes the information collected during registration for and through Your use of the Service, how We use it, how We share it, how We protect it, and the choices You can make about Your information. All references throughout this Privacy Policy to “Flipp” shall include all Flipp affiliates, and all services, applications or platforms owned and operated by Flipp and/or such affiliates.
ATTENTION: PLEASE READ OUR PRIVACY POLICY CAREFULLY BEFORE DOWNLOADING OR USING THE SERVICE.  DOWNLOADING OR USING THE SERVICE INDICATES THAT YOU ACCEPT AND AGREE TO BE BOUND BY THIS PRIVACY POLICY IN FULL. IF YOU DO NOT ACCEPT THIS PRIVACY POLICY, DO NOT DOWNLOAD OR USE THE SERVICE. You acknowledge (a) that You have read and understood this Privacy Policy; and (b) this Privacy Policy shall have the same force and effect as a signed agreement.
Unless explicitly stated otherwise, any new features that augment or enhance the current Service shall be subject to this Privacy Policy.
Please review the Privacy Policy each time You use the Service.  BY USING THE SERVICE, YOU AGREE TO BE BOUND BY THE MOST RECENT VERSION OF THE PRIVACY POLICY.  If We materially change this Privacy Policy, We’ll let You know by showing it to You again when You access the Service and/or updating the apps.
CROSS-BORDER TRANSFER OF INFORMATION:
Please note that the Service is hosted in the United States and Flipp is headquartered in Canada, and additionally Flipp uses service providers in the United States, Europe, and Canada.  Therefore, Your information, including any personal information provided pursuant to the Service, may be processed and stored in the United States, Europe, and Canada. As a result, United States or European federal and state governments, Canadian federal or provincial courts or law enforcement or regulatory agencies may be able to obtain disclosure of Your information through laws applicable in the United States, Europe, and Canada. Additionally, some of our service providers use subcontractors or service providers outside of these listed jurisdictions, so there are limited instances in which processing and storage of your personal information may occur outside of the United States, Europe, and Canada. Your use of the Service or Your submission of any information to Us will constitute Your consent to the transfer of Your information outside of Your country of residence, which may provide for different data protection rules than in Your country. Please contact Us at
privacy@flipp.com
if You have any questions about how Your information may be processed or stored in the United States, Europe, or Canada.
I. Information We Collect
Consent
As permitted by law, Your consent may be implied by Your use of the Service and Your acceptance of, and agreement to, this Privacy Policy. We may seek consent to use and disclose Your personal information after it has been collected in those cases where We wish to use the information for a new or different purpose where You have not already consented to such a use of Your personal information.
In most cases and subject to legal and contractual restrictions, You are free to refuse or withdraw Your consent at any time upon reasonable, advance notice to privacy@flipp.com. It should be noted that in certain circumstances, the Service can only be offered if you provide Us with Your personal information. Consequently, if You choose not provide Us with the required personal information, we may not be able to offer You the Service.
Information You Provide to Us
We may collect identifiers from You when You register for and use the Service, contact or interact with us, fill out a form, and voluntarily provide Us with Your comments and other content in connection with using the Service.  When calling us, Your telephone number and name may be collected.
When You register on the Website or the Apps, We may collect identifiers including Your name, email address, telephone number, address, IP address, password, and any other information that You provide in the registration process. We may associate commercial information with you including shopping lists, receipts and any other information You provide with Your registered profile.
When You submit a “Contact Us” form, We collect identifiers including Your name, phone number, email address, and any other information You choose to provide to Us.
When You create a support ticket, We collect identifiers including Your email address and any other information You choose to provide to Us.
When You enter contests or respond to promotions, We may collect identifiers and commercial information included in Your entry information such as name, email address, physical address, phone number, age, photo, videos, social account information and any other information You provide.
When You add a loyalty card to your account, redeem a coupon or otherwise interact with a company with which You have a loyalty account, We may collect commercial information and identifiers including Your Loyalty ID and/or Loyalty account number.
When You apply for a job through the Service, We may collect identifiers, education information, and professional or employment-related information including: Your name, email address, telephone number, current employer, social media account links, and any information You provide through Your responses to questions posed or in Your cover letter, resume or otherwise through the Careers/Job Openings section of the Flipp.com Website.
Information We Collect Automatically When You Use the Service
We may automatically collect identifiers, commercial information, audio, electronic, visual, or other similar information, geolocation information, internet or other electronic network activity information, and inferences drawn from all of the above, regarding each user of our Service, including: Your location, Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, NFC (near field communication) or other connection information, network connection information, Internet Protocol (IP) address, telephone number, browser and device information, advertising identifiers, the domain name of Your Internet search provider, the Service features You use, and the time of Your use.  For App users, We may read, modify or delete content on Your device and enable Your device to take pictures or videos (such as to submit a photo of a receipt in connection with claiming a rebate).  We may also collect information about Your access to and use of the Services via third party service providers, as described in the Third Parties that Provide Content, Advertising Services, or Functionality on or for Our Service section below.
Information We Collect from Other Sources
We may collect information including identifiers, geolocation, and commercial information about You from third party sources including, but not limited to, social media companies, advertising partners, measurement partners, third party websites, retailers, CPGs, and food service companies, and our employment services provider(s). This information includes Your personal information (such as Your address, e-mail address, social media identifiers, device or advertiser IDs, IP address, and customer or account IDs), location data, online activity (including purchase history), and the same types of information we collect when You use the Service through our Website or Apps. Examples of specific partners and the kinds of information we collect can be found in this section.
Social Media
The Website and the Apps provide connections with Facebook, Twitter, Google, Pinterest, and LinkedIn.  If You connect with Facebook through the Service, We receive Your public profile (which includes Your Facebook User ID, Your profile photo, Your public information, and Your friends’ User IDs), Your language, Your country, and whether You are in an age group, for instance, under 18, between 18-20, or 21 and over, and any other information Facebook provides.  We can also access, store, and update the information You share through Facebook.  If You connect with Twitter through the Service, We receive Your Twitter identity (which includes Your Twitter avatar and user name and Your followers’ user names).  We can also access, store, and update the information You share through Twitter.  If You sign in through Google, We receive Your public profile and Your email address.  If you sign in through Pinterest, we receive your public profile information.
Advertising Partners
We may receive information about You from other digital advertising companies with which We work (“Advertising Partners”) to help Us deliver ads to You and recognize You across browsers and devices. This may include pseudonymous advertiser identifiers that some companies or third party ad platforms choose to share with us, such as Your “Customer ID” with a company or an identifier associated with a hashed version of Your email address. We may work with these Advertising Partners to synchronize their unique, anonymous identifiers to our own to enhance data points about a particular unique browser or device.
Flipp works with LiveRamp which allows companies to integrate their customer records with online advertising (also known as CRM onboarding).  We may receive a hashed version of Your information from LiveRamp, to enable better targeted advertising where LiveRamp already possesses Your email address, device ID, or other advertising ID.
Through our marketing automation service provider, Salesforce, we collect information including IP address, operating system, browser, pages visited when You indicate interest in our services through their service.  Information about Salesforce’s  privacy practices is available here:
https://www.salesforce.com/company/privacy/
.
We also use Zendesk for marketing automation services and through them collect IP address, email, name and pages visited when you contact us through their service. Information about Zendesk’s privacy practices are available here:
https://www.zendesk.com/company/agreements-and-terms/privacy-notice/
and here:
https://support.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/4408837672346-Default-Data-Types-Captured-by-Zendesk-Services
.
Community Engagement
When you participate in our community engagement panel provided in association with Alida, We may receive information about You to assist us with reviewing and responding to any feedback or comments You provide. Alida’s privacy policy is here:
https://www.alida.com/privacy-policy
, and information about their cookie policy and opt-out can be found here:
https://www.alida.com/cookie-policy
.
Third Parties and Partners
When You access the Service through a third party website, such as a retailer or media company, We may receive the same types of information about You as We receive when You use the Service through our website or Apps.
We may also receive information about You from our partners, such as their CRM data about You or transaction information collected at the point of purchase. We may receive Your location information when You enter or are near one of our partners’ stores such as Your device’s GPS, Bluetooth, NFC or other communications signal and information about nearby WiFi networks, cell towers, and other communications infrastructure.
Employment Services
We use Greenhouse for online employment applications. Greenhouse’s privacy policy is available here:
https://www.greenhouse.com/privacy-policy.
We may receive personal information about You from Greenhouse as described in Section III(B) below.
We may combine all of the information We collect from or about You and draw inferences from such information, and further use it in the manner described in this Privacy Policy.
II. How We Use Your Information
We use the information that We collect for several business and commercial purposes, including:
The purposes for which You provided it;
To provide services to You;
To provide user verification services;
To create or update Your account;
To connect with Your social media accounts and post content You choose to share;
To process and respond to Your inquiries and comments;
To send You information about Your relationship or transactions with us;
To develop new products and services;
To personalize and enhance Your experience using the Service;
To personalize and enhance Your shopping experience;
To send notifications through the Apps;
As permitted by law, to send periodic emails. The email address You provide may be used to send You information and updates pertaining to Your account, in addition to receiving occasional company news, updates, related product or service information, etc.  Note: If at any time You would like to unsubscribe from receiving future emails, We include detailed unsubscribe instructions at the bottom of each email;
To generate and review reports and data about our user base and service usage patterns;
To compile aggregate data for internal and external business purposes;
To display relevant advertising and remarketing across websites;
To prevent fraud and abuse of the Service and to otherwise protect users and visitors and our business;
To administer, operate and improve the Service and for internal business purposes;
To assist law enforcement and respond to subpoenas; and
To perform other business activities as needed, or as described elsewhere in this Privacy Policy.
As explained elsewhere in this Privacy Policy, personal information We collect may be processed by our partners in providing related services to the Service (such as administration services, technical services relating to the maintenance, servicing, and upgrading of the products, software, hosting services, data migration services and analytical services, among others).
For the purposes of the
California Consumer Privacy Act of 2018
(the “
CCPA 2018
“), as amended by the
California Privacy Rights Act of 2020
(the “
CRPA
“, and together with the CCPA 2018, the “
CCPA
“), We collect and use your identifiers, commercial information, and geolocation information for internal business purposes including:
Auditing related to a current interaction with you and concurrent transactions including, but not limited to, counting ad impressions to unique visitors, verifying positioning and quality of ad impressions, and auditing compliance with the CCPA and other standards;
Detecting security incidents, protecting against malicious, deceptive, fraudulent, or illegal activity, and prosecuting those responsible for that activity;
Debugging to identify and repair errors that impair existing intended functionality;
Performing services to you including maintaining or servicing accounts, providing customer service, processing or fulfilling orders and transactions, verifying customer information, processing payments, providing financing, providing advertising or marketing services, providing analytic services, or providing similar services; and
Undertaking internal research for technological development and demonstration.
Ad Choices / Do Not Share My Personal Information
Flipp may partner with companies to provide you with interest-based or online behavioural advertising in order to serve you with the most relevant content and advertising. To learn more about interest based advertising, or if you would like to opt-out of receiving such ads at participating websites, please visit the Digital Advertising Alliance’s website at
http://youradchoices.ca/choices/
or
www.aboutads.info
.
III. How Your Information is Disclosed
Information may be disclosed to third parties in accordance with our Privacy Policy, including our service providers and business partners, employment service providers, partners, media companies, and advertising partners. In certain instances and jurisdictions, this disclosure may be deemed to be a sale of your personal information. This information includes Your personal information (such as Your address, e-mail address, social media identifiers, device or advertiser IDs, IP address, and customer or account IDs), location data, and information about Your use of the Service. Examples of specific partners and the kinds of information we disclose can be found in this section. Please note that a user may choose not to share certain information as described in Your Choices Regarding Your Information below, and certain jurisdictions have specific rights that are also called out in Section XIV below.
A. Third Party Service Providers and Business Partners
We may use third party service providers and business partners to perform functions in connection with the Service, such as coupon processing, rebate processing and payment, site analytics, remarketing, and functions related to analyzing and improving the Service usefulness, reliability, user experience, and operation, advertising, storing data, providing users with products and services, and as otherwise described in this Privacy Policy. We also may share users’ personal information with advertisers for their direct marketing and promotional purposes and so they can provide services to you. We may use remarketing cookies or pixels from Google and Facebook and share some of your personal information with Facebook and Google for use in advertising. For information on how you can disable these cookies, see Section IIIE below.
We use Alida as our community engagement partner, and we may share some of your personal information and information about your interactions with the Services with Alida if you choose to participate in a community panel. Alida’s privacy policy is
here
, and information about their cookie policy and opt-out can be found
here
.
B. Job Openings
We use a third-party service provider, Greenhouse, to collect information on the Job Openings Page and the storage, sharing, and use of that information is governed by its privacy policy, which you can review
here
.
If you are interested in pursuing career opportunities within the United States or Canada, you can review and apply for job openings listed in an online jobs database. If you elect to proceed, you will be seamlessly linked to a website maintained by Greenhouse, headquartered in New York, U.S. As we are not responsible for the content, data collection or privacy policies of Greenhouse, we urge you to read the privacy and security policies of Greenhouse (see link above) before providing any personal information.
If you choose to apply online for a posted job that is linked to the Greenhouse website, you will be required to provide your name, email address, current employer, a resume, and responses to questions posed on the site. Your responses to these questions will be used in evaluating your qualifications for a position. Please do not include your social security number/social insurance number, credit card or bank account numbers, and non-work related personal information such as eye color, marital status, etc.
At the beginning of the application process, you will be asked to provide your email address. If you do not have an email address, please contact Human Resources at 1-844-204-2900 or
HR@flipp.com
.
The personal information that you submit to Greenhouse while online may be accessed and downloaded by Flipp professionals located in the U.S. and Canada through a secured connection to the Greenhouse database and used for evaluating your qualifications for the job for which you have applied and other jobs that may suit your experience and qualifications. In addition, the provisions of this policy relating to use of information apply to any information that may be accessed or downloaded by Flipp from the Greenhouse database.
You may receive emails from Greenhouse about your application, such as an email thanking you for submitting your resume.
Other than with Greenhouse, we do not share resume or application information with third parties without specific authorization from you.
